  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This randomized clinical trial was conducted to examine and compare the effectiveness of
      pulpotomy in primary molars treated with calcium silicate based materials including
      Biodentine and two different mineral trioxide aggregate (MTA) products (white ProRoot® MTA
      and MTA Plus®). Ferric sulfate pulpotomy was selected to represent the control group. 116
      primary molars in 29 children were treated by pulpotomy and followed for a period of 24
      months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
